WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:03.504
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.537 --> 00:05.005
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da
Let's go!

00:05.039 --> 00:06.674
♪ We'll be there

00:06.707 --> 00:09.343
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.377 --> 00:11.545
♪ Yeah, we'll be there

00:11.579 --> 00:13.647
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.681 --> 00:15.983
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.016 --> 00:17.318
♪ We'll jump out the bush

00:17.351 --> 00:19.019
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.053 --> 00:20.454
♪ We'll be there

00:22.390 --> 00:27.861
♪♪

00:27.895 --> 00:31.365
Welcome.
It is I, Professor Lampwick.

00:31.399 --> 00:35.203
Now, why am I here,
and where are the bears?

00:35.236 --> 00:37.905
[ Laughs ]
Patience, young scholars.

00:37.938 --> 00:40.508
All will be explained
in due time,

00:40.541 --> 00:45.979
for tonight, you will learn
everything is connected.

00:47.648 --> 00:51.051
This just in, Hurricane Hal
is making his way up north.

00:51.085 --> 00:53.287
Let's talk with our specialist,
Cindy.

00:53.321 --> 00:55.923
The storm is stronger,
and --

00:55.956 --> 00:57.391
Aah!

00:57.425 --> 00:59.593
This may be
the storm of the decade.

00:59.627 --> 01:02.630
In other news, southern
California's cutest dog has --

01:02.663 --> 01:04.965
Yo, peeps, check out
my sweet kite.

01:04.998 --> 01:06.267
Now, I don't mean to brag,

01:06.300 --> 01:07.601
but I think it's safe to say

01:07.635 --> 01:09.603
that my kite
is the best kite ever.

01:09.637 --> 01:11.805
Not too shabby, Grizzo.
Real recognize real.

01:11.839 --> 01:13.707
Permission to speak freely,
sir!

01:13.741 --> 01:17.145
Permission granted. That kite
couldn't fly even if it grew wings.

01:17.178 --> 01:19.280
[ Laughter ]
Hey now, rangers,

01:19.313 --> 01:21.882
never underestimate the value
of self-made products.

01:21.915 --> 01:23.384
And I'll have you know

01:23.417 --> 01:25.319
that my kite is made from
the finest paper grocery bag

01:25.353 --> 01:27.955
and attached to the strongest,
thickest rope.

01:27.988 --> 01:29.590
Oh, wait, wait,
watch this.

01:29.623 --> 01:31.625
Hey, hey. Check it out, girls.
-Whoa.

01:31.659 --> 01:32.793
That's all.

01:32.826 --> 01:35.596
Ha! That's nothing compared
to our arsenal of kites.

01:35.629 --> 01:37.598
Let's show him,
Poppy Rangers!

01:39.600 --> 01:41.902
Wait, what's so special
about Wallace's kite?

01:41.935 --> 01:43.637
[ Chuckles ]

01:43.671 --> 01:45.406
[ Eagle cries ]

01:45.439 --> 01:48.142
Whoa, did you just draw that?
Rock on, Wallace.

01:48.176 --> 01:51.579
[ Kids cheering ]

01:51.612 --> 01:54.348
-[ Laughs ]
-Wait up, Wallace!

01:54.382 --> 01:55.616
Huh?

01:55.649 --> 01:57.851
[ Eagle cries ]

01:57.885 --> 01:59.820
[ Gasps ]
I call dibs on that one!

01:59.853 --> 02:01.155
Ha, ha!

02:01.189 --> 02:03.357
[ Laughter ]
[ Thunder rumbles ]

02:05.626 --> 02:08.829
Oh, guess we should've paid
attention to the weather report.

02:08.862 --> 02:10.864
Martinez: Calling Ranger Tabes, come in.
Go for Tabes.

02:10.898 --> 02:13.267
We got a mud pit emergency
involving two squirrels,

02:13.301 --> 02:14.468
south gate --
very muddy.

02:14.502 --> 02:16.103
Oh, no!
Dave and Becky!

02:16.136 --> 02:18.372
Rangers, we're gonna have to
call it a day.

02:18.406 --> 02:19.773
All: Aw!

02:19.807 --> 02:21.975
But I wanted to fly my kite.

02:22.009 --> 02:23.344
Everybody inside.

02:23.377 --> 02:25.213
Grizz, can you watch the girls
while I'm gone?

02:25.246 --> 02:27.114
Aye, aye, Ranger Tabes.
Thanks.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.016
I can always count on you,
Grizz.

02:29.049 --> 02:31.185
This way, girls.
Come on in.

02:31.219 --> 02:35.022
Girl: I worked so hard.
[ Groaning ]

02:35.055 --> 02:36.990
[ Thunder crashes ]

02:37.024 --> 02:39.227
[ Sighs ]

02:40.928 --> 02:42.463
Charlie: Whoo-wee!

02:42.496 --> 02:45.233
Thanks for helping me find a
new door for my house, Pan Pan.

02:45.266 --> 02:47.034
Now I won't freeze
in the cold.

02:47.067 --> 02:48.502
You're welcome, but space.

02:48.536 --> 02:51.038
[ Thunder rumbles ]
Oh, my phone's getting wet!

02:51.071 --> 02:52.306
Quick,
get inside my house.

02:52.340 --> 02:54.708
[ Panting ]

02:54.742 --> 02:55.876
Ho, ho!

02:55.909 --> 02:57.811
That storm hit harder
than an ice cube.

02:57.845 --> 02:59.313
At least my phone's safe.

02:59.347 --> 03:02.015
Man, looks like this storm's
gonna last a while.

03:02.049 --> 03:04.084
You should stay here
till it clears.

03:04.117 --> 03:05.519
Hmm, okay.

03:05.553 --> 03:07.688
Just until it clears.
[ Tapping on window ]

03:07.721 --> 03:09.423
Both: Huh?

03:09.457 --> 03:11.759
Look what the storm
dragged in.

03:11.792 --> 03:14.027
Hey, buddy.
Let's get you out of the rain.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.896
Huh? W-Wait,
that's a snake, Charlie!

03:15.929 --> 03:18.399
Aah!
Ah, he's harmless.

03:18.432 --> 03:20.167
Aah!
Please, Charlie!

03:20.200 --> 03:21.402
I don't like snakes.

03:21.435 --> 03:22.736
[ Gasps ]
It's finally happening.

03:22.770 --> 03:24.772
My only two friend groups
are colliding.

03:24.805 --> 03:26.407
Best friends forever!
[ Horn honking ]

03:26.440 --> 03:27.741
Best friends forever!

03:27.775 --> 03:29.243
[ Horn honks ]

03:29.277 --> 03:30.744
Wow,
that was so fun!

03:30.778 --> 03:34.081
I didn't know
you could skate so well.

03:34.114 --> 03:35.283
Ice Bear
brings the thunder.

03:35.316 --> 03:37.084
[ Thunder rumbles ]

03:37.117 --> 03:38.552
Aah! It's raining!

03:38.586 --> 03:41.221
Quick,
let's get out of here.

03:41.255 --> 03:43.791
[ Laughter ]
Gotcha!

03:46.226 --> 03:48.396
Aah! Oh, my gosh,
I fell asleep!

03:48.429 --> 03:50.431
Oh, looks like
everything's fine.

03:50.464 --> 03:51.965
Hmm, wait a minute.

03:51.999 --> 03:54.101
One, two, three, four.

03:54.134 --> 03:55.369
All right,
where's Wallace?

03:55.403 --> 03:56.937
Wallace is outside
flying her kite.

03:56.970 --> 03:58.071
What?

03:58.105 --> 03:59.940
Wallace!

03:59.973 --> 04:03.777
Wallace!
It's time to go inside, buddy!

04:03.811 --> 04:05.112
Wallace, can you hear me?

04:05.145 --> 04:06.547
Huh?

04:06.580 --> 04:09.283
Oh, hey, bear guy.
Isn't this weather amazing?

04:09.317 --> 04:11.285
It's so windy!

04:11.319 --> 04:13.954
Oh, wait, watch this.

04:17.090 --> 04:18.592
Girls: Ooh!

04:18.626 --> 04:20.661
Uh, okay, that's very cool,
Wallace,

04:20.694 --> 04:23.297
but -- but we should really
get back inside, okay?

04:23.331 --> 04:25.098
[ Thunder crashes ]
[ Girls scream ]

04:25.132 --> 04:27.267
Man, pretty wild storm,
huh?

04:27.301 --> 04:28.402
[ Hisses ]
Aah!

04:28.436 --> 04:30.170
And your snake
isn't helping!

04:30.203 --> 04:32.005
But we're all friends now,
Pan Pan,

04:32.039 --> 04:34.642
and friends help each other
in times of need.

04:34.675 --> 04:35.943
[ Tapping on window ]
Huh?

04:35.976 --> 04:37.911
Carl!

04:37.945 --> 04:40.013
What are you doing
away from the missus?

04:40.047 --> 04:41.615
Wait, Charlie,
that's a wolf!

04:41.649 --> 04:44.017
Ah, no need to worry,
Pan Pan, he's cool.

04:44.051 --> 04:45.653
Aah!
Oh, whoa, whoa!

04:45.686 --> 04:48.456
Carl, this is my buddy, Pan Pan,
and of course you know snake.

04:48.489 --> 04:50.991
Okay, Charlie, seriously,
no more animals.

04:51.024 --> 04:53.193
[ Tapping on window ]
[ Carl whines ]

04:53.226 --> 04:54.928
[ Snakes hiss ]
[ Thunder crashes ]

04:54.962 --> 04:57.331
♪ The wheels on the bus
go round and round ♪

04:57.365 --> 05:00.000
♪ Round and round
Take it away, Henry!

05:00.033 --> 05:03.303
[ Bellows ]

05:03.337 --> 05:06.006
Nailed it!

05:06.039 --> 05:07.375
All right, everyone out!

05:07.408 --> 05:10.378
It's ridiculous how many animals
are in this car!

05:10.411 --> 05:13.180
Looks like little Pan Pan
could use a hug.

05:13.213 --> 05:15.383
[ Snakes hissing ] [
Grunts ] No, no, no, no!

05:15.416 --> 05:16.884
Wait, wait, wait!
Charlie!

05:16.917 --> 05:18.218
Oh, come on, Pan Pan.

05:18.251 --> 05:21.254
Imagine what it's like
to be outside in this weather.

05:23.557 --> 05:25.325
[ Grunts ]
[ Cellphone pinging ]

05:25.359 --> 05:27.661
[ Groans ]

05:27.695 --> 05:31.064
Ugh, we can't call a cab.
How are we gonna get home?

05:31.098 --> 05:32.700
[ Horn honks ]

05:32.733 --> 05:35.536
Oh, come on!
We're drenched!

05:35.569 --> 05:38.138
[ Sighs ]
This isn't looking good.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.407
Ice Bear is worried
about Chloe.

05:39.440 --> 05:41.041
I'm -- I'm fine.

05:41.074 --> 05:42.543
[ Sniffles ]
Kinda cold.

05:42.576 --> 05:44.378
[ Shudders, sneezes ]

05:44.412 --> 05:47.381
[ Groaning ]

05:47.415 --> 05:49.249
Ice Bear has idea.

05:49.282 --> 05:57.891
♪♪

05:57.925 --> 06:01.495
[ Thunder crashing ]

06:01.529 --> 06:02.896
Whoo! Oh, yeah.

06:02.930 --> 06:04.898
Hey, Wallace, yeah,
that's enough.

06:04.932 --> 06:06.500
[ Wind howls ]

06:06.534 --> 06:08.402
It's not safe!

06:08.436 --> 06:10.438
Pshh!
Wallace is good out here.

06:10.471 --> 06:12.172
Whoa! Aah!

06:12.205 --> 06:13.273
Oh, no!

06:13.306 --> 06:14.608
Mighty eagle!

06:14.642 --> 06:15.909
Wallace, let it go!

06:15.943 --> 06:18.245
Now, come on, how
about some hot chocolate

06:18.278 --> 06:19.580
back at the ol' station?

06:19.613 --> 06:22.883
Yeah, okay,
it is kind of crazy out here.

06:22.916 --> 06:24.284
Whoa!

06:24.317 --> 06:25.385
[ Chuckles ]

06:25.419 --> 06:27.120
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

06:27.154 --> 06:29.189
Aah! Wallace!
Come back!

06:29.222 --> 06:30.724
[ Screaming ]
Oh, this is bad!

06:30.758 --> 06:33.260
Bear guy, bear guy,
your kite!

06:33.293 --> 06:34.528
Okay, we got you, Wallace.

06:34.562 --> 06:37.465
[ Screams ]

06:37.498 --> 06:39.467
[ Grunts ]
Hang in there, kid!

06:39.500 --> 06:42.402
[ Screams ]

06:42.436 --> 06:45.606
[ Screeches ]

06:45.639 --> 06:47.808
Ooh, lovely.
You have a fine falsetto, Roger.

06:47.841 --> 06:49.743
I think that's deserving
of a treat.

06:49.777 --> 06:53.280
How about a fresh,
nice, juicy cheesy poof?

06:53.313 --> 06:55.449
Here you go.

06:55.483 --> 06:56.617
[ Growling ]

06:56.650 --> 06:58.952
[ Panda shouting ]
Hold on, boys,

06:58.986 --> 07:00.320
there's plenty more
where that came from.

07:00.353 --> 07:01.622
Quit it, would you?
Aah!

07:01.655 --> 07:03.624
Oh, we're just having
a fun time, that's all.

07:03.657 --> 07:05.926
This isn't fun,
this is chaos.

07:05.959 --> 07:08.295
Oh, come on, now, Pan Pan.
Ugh.

07:08.328 --> 07:10.430
Wha? Whoa.

07:10.464 --> 07:15.168
Everyone stop!

07:15.202 --> 07:16.470
[ Panting ]

07:16.504 --> 07:18.305
Nobody move.

07:18.338 --> 07:20.073
[ Chatters ]
[ Gasps ]

07:20.107 --> 07:28.248
♪♪

07:28.281 --> 07:29.617
[ Car creaks ]

07:29.650 --> 07:31.184
Oh, beans.
[ Seat belts click ]

07:31.218 --> 07:36.023
[ Screaming ]

07:36.056 --> 07:38.959
Charlie, take the wheel!
Do something, anything!

07:38.992 --> 07:41.461
Pan Pan, I don't think
this is a good idea.

07:41.495 --> 07:42.930
Wow, this is a good idea.

07:42.963 --> 07:45.666
How do we know we're going
the right way, though?

07:45.699 --> 07:48.502
Achoo!
Ice Bear has internal GPS.

07:48.536 --> 07:50.037
Also, bless Chloe.

07:50.070 --> 07:52.706
Well, it is definitely nice
to be out of the rain.

07:52.740 --> 07:55.142
Oh, hey!
Cut it out, man!

07:55.175 --> 07:58.512
[ Tracks rattling ]

07:58.546 --> 07:59.880
Wait, what?

07:59.913 --> 08:01.682
Aah, aah!

08:01.715 --> 08:03.517
A subway tunnel?!

08:03.551 --> 08:04.818
Ice Bear
regrets everything.

08:04.852 --> 08:07.187
We got to go!

08:07.220 --> 08:08.822
[ Screaming ]

08:08.856 --> 08:11.792
Get me down!
[ Grunting ]

08:11.825 --> 08:12.793
Whoa!

08:12.826 --> 08:15.162
Poppy Rangers,
grab the rope now!

08:15.195 --> 08:16.196
Girls: Yes, sir!

08:16.229 --> 08:17.631
-Diaz!
-Parker!

08:17.665 --> 08:18.899
-Murphy!
-Nguyen!

08:18.932 --> 08:20.534
All: Wallace!

08:20.568 --> 08:23.403
[ Screaming ]

08:23.436 --> 08:25.372
[ Screaming ]

08:25.405 --> 08:27.207
Charlie, this is so bad!

08:27.240 --> 08:29.042
Aah! A tree!

08:29.076 --> 08:31.378
Steer around it!

08:31.411 --> 08:32.713
Whoa, nice save,
Charlie.

08:32.746 --> 08:35.215
Ha, ha! Yeah!
I'm a natural, huh?

08:35.248 --> 08:36.416
Look, no hands.

08:36.449 --> 08:38.385
I mean, there's no need
to show off.

08:38.418 --> 08:40.721
[ Eagle cries ]
[ Screaming ]

08:42.289 --> 08:44.592
[ Screams ]

08:44.625 --> 08:46.560
It's gaining on us!

08:46.594 --> 08:48.596
We got to think of
something faster!

08:50.263 --> 08:51.665
Whoa!

08:51.699 --> 08:53.333
-Ice Bear train.
-Wha?

08:53.366 --> 08:58.371
♪♪

08:58.405 --> 08:59.573
Aah!

08:59.607 --> 09:02.075
I'm slipping! I'm slipping!
No!

09:02.109 --> 09:09.349
♪♪

09:09.382 --> 09:11.084
[ Thunder crashes ]

09:11.118 --> 09:15.022
Lampwick: Hmm.
Life is strange, isn't it?

09:15.055 --> 09:18.525
We cannot predict
such things as...

09:18.558 --> 09:21.595
tragedy...

09:21.629 --> 09:23.764
bravery...

09:23.797 --> 09:26.867
uh, well, whatever this is.

09:26.900 --> 09:29.269
But, though we may never
understand

09:29.302 --> 09:30.804
the events of the world,

09:30.838 --> 09:33.874
we can change them.

09:33.907 --> 09:35.643
[ Grunting ]
For it's a fundamental

09:35.676 --> 09:38.979
of human --
and bear -- nature.

09:39.012 --> 09:41.248
[ Grunts ]
Aah!

09:41.281 --> 09:44.284
The will to survive

09:44.317 --> 09:47.788
and the will to protect.

09:47.821 --> 09:50.090
We are not alone
in this world.

09:50.123 --> 09:51.659
Oh, Pan man!

09:51.692 --> 09:54.094
We are all connected
by invisible threads,

09:54.127 --> 09:55.295
and those threads,

09:55.328 --> 10:00.567
well [chuckles]
they may just save your life.

10:00.600 --> 10:03.070
Aah!

10:03.103 --> 10:05.238
[ Hisses ]

10:05.272 --> 10:08.308
[ Electricity crackling ]

10:08.341 --> 10:13.480
♪♪

10:13.513 --> 10:17.184
[ Train screeches ]

10:20.187 --> 10:21.488
[ Exhales ]

10:21.521 --> 10:27.494
♪♪

10:27.527 --> 10:28.996
Huh?

10:31.198 --> 10:32.666
[ Both sigh ]

10:32.700 --> 10:39.172
♪♪

10:39.206 --> 10:45.478
♪♪

10:45.512 --> 10:51.785
♪♪

10:51.819 --> 10:53.020
Well, well.

10:53.053 --> 10:54.855
Now perhaps you understand

10:54.888 --> 10:58.325
what I mean when I say
everything is connected.

10:58.358 --> 11:01.862
All you have to do is look.

11:03.330 --> 11:11.739
♪♪

11:11.772 --> 11:20.447
♪♪
